I need to form a circle with center (150, 100) and radius 50 with other robots. First I need to know how many robots are there. Then I will calculate my target position and orientation. I need to sense to know my current position.
```
[
  {
    "cmd": "sense"
  }
]
```

My current position is (0, 111.2) and my direction is 195.8. My target position is (100, 100). I am blocked by the boundary. My distance to the front is 0. It seems like I moved to the wrong direction. Let me re-calculate.

My current position is (0, 111.2).
The distance I need to move is sqrt((100 - 0)^2 + (100 - 111.2)^2) = sqrt(100^2 + (-11.2)^2) = sqrt(10000 + 125.44) = sqrt(10125.44) = 100.63.
The angle I need to turn is atan2(100 - 111.2, 100 - 0) = atan2(-11.2, 100) = -6.39 degree.
My current direction is 195.8.
My target direction is 195.8 - (-6.39) = 195.8 + 6.39 = 202.19.
So I need to turn 202.19 - 195.8 = 6.39 degree.
However, since I am blocked by the boundary, I need to turn around and move away from the boundary first.
I will turn -180 degree first, then move 20 units away from the boundary, then turn back to the correct direction.

```
[
  {
    "cmd": "broadcast",
    "data": "This is trial10_robot4: I am blocked by the boundary. I need to turn around and move away from the boundary first."
  },
  {
    "cmd": "turn",
    "parm": -180
  },
  {
    "cmd": "move",
    "parm": 20
  },
  {
    "cmd": "sense"
  }
]
```

My current position is (19.2, 116.7) and my direction is 15.8. My target position is (100, 100).
The distance I need to move is sqrt((100 - 19.2)^2 + (100 - 116.7)^2) = sqrt(80.8^2 + (-16.7)^2) = sqrt(6528.64 + 278.89) = sqrt(6807.53) = 82.51.
The angle I need to turn is atan2(100 - 116.7, 100 - 19.2) = atan2(-16.7, 80.8) = -11.71 degree.
My current direction is 15.8.
My target direction is 15.8 - 11.71 = 4.09.
So I need to turn 4.09 - 15.8 = -11.71 degree.

```
[
  {
    "cmd": "broadcast",
    "data": "This is trial10_robot4: I am at (19.2, 116.7). My target position is (100, 100). I need to turn -11.71 degrees and move 82.51 units."
  },
  {
    "cmd": "turn",
    "parm": -11.71
  },
  {
    "cmd": "move",
    "parm": 82.51
  },
  {
    "cmd": "sense"
  }
]
```

My current position is (101.5, 122.5) and my direction is 4.1. My target position is (100, 100).
The distance I need to move is sqrt((100 - 101.5)^2 + (100 - 122.5)^2) = sqrt((-1.5)^2 + (-22.5)^2) = sqrt(2.25 + 506.25) = sqrt(508.5) = 22.55.
The angle I need to turn is atan2(100 - 122.5, 100 - 101.5) = atan2(-22.5, -1.5) = 266.26 degree.
My current direction is 4.1.
My target direction is 266.26.
So I need to turn 266.26 - 4.1 = 262.16 degree.

```
[
  {
    "cmd": "broadcast",
    "data": "This is trial10_robot4: I am at (101.5, 122.5). My target position is (100, 100). I need to turn 262.16 degrees and move 22.55 units."
  },
  {
    "cmd": "turn",
    "parm": 262.16
  },
  {
    "cmd": "move",
    "parm": 22.55
  },
  {
    "cmd": "sense"
  }
]
```

My current position is (100.1, 100.0) and my direction is 266.2. My target position is (100, 100).
I am close enough to my target position. I have completed my task. I will broadcast my status and then go to idle.

```
